quran[17]{c,v,t,f}:
52,15,"Is this, then, any feat of magic or are you unable to see? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
52,16,"Go now and burn in it. It is all the same whether you bear it patiently or do not bear it with patience. You are only being recompensed for your deeds.”"
52,17,"Surely the God-fearing {1} shall be in Gardens and bliss,",footnotes:1:“The righteous”: the people who believed in the news given by the Prophets and who safeguarded themselves in the world itself and refrained from thoughts and deeds that doom man to Hell.
52,18,"enjoying what Allah will have endowed them with; and their Lord will have saved them from the torment of the Blazing Fire. {1}",footnotes:1:There seems to be no need to mention a person’s being saved from Hell after it has been said that he will be admitted to Heaven
52,19,"(They will be told): “Eat and drink to your hearts' {1} content as a reward for your deeds.”",footnotes:1:Here
52,20,"The God-fearing shall be reclining on couches facing each other, and We shall wed them to maidens with large, beautiful eyes. {1}",footnotes:1:For explanation
52,21,"We shall unite the believers with those descendants of theirs who followed them in their faith, and shall not deny them any part of the reward for their good deeds. {1} Every person is pledged to what he did. {2}",footnotes:1:Here
52,22,"We shall provide them in abundance with all kinds of fruit and meat, {1} whatever they may desire.",footnotes:1:In this verse
52,23,"They shall pass on to one another a cup that will incite neither levity nor sin. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
52,24,"Youths as fair as hidden pearls will be set apart to wait upon them; they will be running to and fro to serve them. {1}",footnotes:1:Here
52,25,"They will turn to one another and ask (regarding the past events)."
52,26,"They will say: “When we were living before among our kinsfolk we lived in constant fear (of Allah's displeasure). {1}",footnotes:1:That is
52,27,"Then Allah graced us with His favour and saved us from the chastisement of the scorching wind. {1}",footnotes:1:The word samum in the original means hot
52,28,"Formerly we had always prayed to Him. Surely He is Most Benign, Most Compassionate.”"
52,29,"So exhort (them, O Prophet), for by your Lord's Grace, you are neither a soothsayer nor a madman. {1}",footnotes:1:After depicting a scene of the Hereafter the address now turns to the obduracy of the disbelieves of Makkah with which they were resisting the message of the Prophet (peace be upon him). This verse though apparently addressed to the Prophet (peace be upon him) is actually meant for the disbelievers through him. Whenever he spoke of Resurrection and the gathering together of mankind
52,30,"Or do they say: “He is a poet for whom we await an adverse turn of fortune.” {1}",footnotes:1:That is
52,31,"Tell them: “Wait; I too am waiting with you.” {1}",footnotes:1:This can have two meanings: (1) I would also see whether this desire of yours is fulfilled or not. (2) I am also waiting to see who goes to his doom
